720927f-a.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 25th Street
720927f-a.text:
Remodelling 69th Regiment Armory, Lexington Avenue,west side, from
26th to 25th Streets.
June 3, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

720926f-a.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 25th Street
720926f-a.text:
54-8 Lexington Avenue at S.W. corner of 25th Street, showing 50 and
52 Lexington Avenue aojoining on the south. Before 1920 this
4-story house will be replaced by a 7-story office building.
About 1912.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

720929f-a.title: Manhattan: Lexington Avenue - 25th Street
720929f-a.text:
61 to 77 Lexington Ave., east side, north from East 25th to 26th
Streets, showing the Hotel Belmore, No. 61-63, at the N.E. corner of
East 25th Street.
July 1937.
George D. Chinn.
O REPRODUCTIONS.
